INSTALL odoo IN WINDOW

download odoo community sourcode
https://github.com/odoo/odoo/tree/15.0

download git 

open in odoo folder git bash

to open vscode git bash
 
code .

follow by this instruction
https://www.surekhatech.com/blog/how-to-install-odoo-in-windows

if you forget postgres password
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wfxrRxzm8jY

in pgadmin
create database 
create login and role
select owner odoo
default postgres port 5432

add path git and postgres in system environment

to check postgres and git version in git bash

psql --version
git --version


to install pyenv in powershell

Invoke-WebRequest -UseBasicParsing -Uri "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pyenv-win/pyenv-win/master/pyenv-win/install-pyenv-win.ps1" -OutFile "./install-pyenv-win.ps1"; &"./install-pyenv-win.ps1"
if error,

Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser

pyenv install --list

to check install pyenv python 

pyenv versions

pyenv install 3.7.9

first in C to set>>

python global 3.7.9

next time check > 

python --version

in cd path odoo folder

python -m venv venv3.7.9

.\venv\Scripts\activate

python --version

pip install setuptools wheel

pip install -r requirements.txt

python odoo-bin -r db_user -w db_password --addons-path=addons -d demo_db

db_user >>odoo
db_password>odoo
default db_port >> 8069

next step

localhost:8069

finally you'll feel GOD.

change odoo config
https://www.cybrosys.com/blog/analysis-of-conf-file-parameters-in-the-odoo-16
